SUMMARY: Character and Voice: A Writing Workshop
DESCRIPTION:In this workshop\, acclaimed writer Janet Burroway will lead 
 participants in creating memorable characters with emphasis on their uniq
 ue voice. Burroway will use examples from her new novel\, Simone in Piece
 s\, to illustrate how voice helps establish a character's history\, desir
 es\, thoughts\, and emotions. Participants will spend time with playful w
 riting prompts meant to tap into their character's voice.\n\nThe workshop
  will take place from 6:00-7:30 PM. Attendees are encouraged to come earl
 y for a pre-event Happy Hour at the MiniBar from 5:30-6:00 PM.\n\nBasic a
 dmission for the class is $35. Admission plus Burroway's seminal craft bo
 ok Writing Fiction: A Guide to Narrative Craft https://bookendsandbeginni
 ngs.com/book/9780226616698 is $50.\n\nJanet Burroway\, is the author of S
 IMONE IN PIECES https://bookendsandbeginnings.com/book/9780299353841 (Nov
 ember\, 2025\; University of Wisconsin Press). She is also the author of 
 WRITING FICTION: A GUIDE TO NARRATIVE CRAFT https://bookendsandbeginnings
 .com/book/9780226616698 \, and has written eight previous novels\, as wel
 l as a memoir\, plays\, short fiction\, children’s books\, and more. Reci
 pient of the Florida Humanities Council’s Lifetime Achievement Award in W
 riting\, she is also the Robert O. Lawton Distinguished Professor Emerita
  at Florida State University at Tallahassee.
CATEGORIES:Downtown
