SUMMARY: Writing the Romance Novel: From Meet Cutes to Happily-Ever-After
 s
DESCRIPTION:Do you love reading about love? You’re not alone. Romance is 
 the bestselling fiction genre by far\, and accounts for more than a billi
 on dollars in book sales a year. It's one of the few book genres that are
  growing their audience\, and there's never been a better time than now t
 o write your own romance novel.\n\nAll you need to get started is an unde
 rstanding of the basic building blocks of a good romance novel: a high co
 ncept premise\, romance tropes (rivals-to-lovers\, grumpy-sunshine\, forc
 ed proximity\, second chance\, oh my!)\, the not-so-easy to write sex sce
 ne (closed door\, or open\, is up to you)\, and of course the non-negotia
 ble Happily Ever After (HEA).\n\nAll participants receive a paperback cop
 y of Love and Other Words https://bookendsandbeginnings.com/book/97815011
 28011 \, by Christina Lauren. We’ll dissect how this New York Times bests
 elling romance writing duo make the most of tropes and chemistry in their
  sizzling bestsellers.\n\nCara Tanamachi (who also writes as Cara Lockwoo
 d) is the award-winning USA Today bestselling author of more than 38 book
 s\, including The Takeover https://bookendsandbeginnings.com/book/9781250
 842282 (St. Martin’s Press\, 2024)\, which received a starred review from
  Publisher’s Weekly. Her first novel\, I Do\, (But I Don't) https://booke
 ndsandbeginnings.com/book/9780743457538 (Simon and Schuster\, 2003)\, was
  made into a Lifetime Original Movie starring Denise Richards (and is now
  streaming on Amazon Prime). Her Valentine’s Day romance\, The Second You
 're Single https://bookendsandbeginnings.com/book/9781250842268 (St. Mart
 in’s Press\, 2023) won the Diverse Writers and Readers International Roma
 nce Book Literary Award in 2024\, and earned a Library Journal starred re
 view. She also wrote the novelization of the Hallmark movie\, The Dater's
  Handbook\, starring the Duchess Meghan Markle. She’s a writing coach and
  editor who’s helped hundreds of authors fulfill their dream of becoming 
 published authors. Read more about her at caratheauthor.com https://carat
 heauthor.com https://urldefense.proofpoint.com/v2/url?u=https-3A__carathe
 author.com_&d=DwMFaQ&c=euGZstcaTDllvimEN8b7jXrwqOf-v5A_CdpgnVfiiMM&r=IVAE
 MmcD_LCs7fmmKBTCJUTKxSNVSxukBJKMohqwvxBepgGgYlmYPbFYVLjPrsRh&m=DBzy6aETmO
 vZL6tqHiBTToejfybImbGW99vmhK80o2NMCPJlMRI-wCTkV8i6db1q&s=7ZxnOIX4Rvyhu2B2
 A_k3y_ob3z9o1JOIFo1ClgFC0DM&e= /.
CATEGORIES:
