SUMMARY: PreK-4th Grade Caregiver Sex Education Workshop: It's That Easy
DESCRIPTION:This workshop is for parents\, caregivers\, and family member
 s who want to deepen their knowledge about healthy sexual development\, s
 exual identity\, and relationships and how to begin discussions on these 
 topics in age-appropriate ways with their children . Participate in a lit
 tle bit of sex ed while your students receive it in school!\n\nLed by Hal
 lie Cohen\, Training and Prevention Coordinator for YWCA Evanston/North S
 hore and sex education consultant to D65\, this workshop will be an engag
 ing\, interactive\, and discussion-based. During this workshop\, particip
 ants will:\n\n  * Explain how their own experience with sexuality educati
 on impacts how and what they share with their own children\;\n  * Identif
 y the most important values and messages they would like to pass on to th
 eir children about sexuality\;\n  * Gain an understanding of healthy sexu
 al development for their child’s age range\;\n  * Identify teachable mome
 nts during which they can share information and family values regarding s
 exuality.\n\nThis workshop will be held twice\, with the focus being on d
 ifferent age groups. If you are unable to attend the date with the ideal 
 focus for you\, feel free to register for the other date. You will surely
  get a lot out of it\, and some of the material will be the same.\n\n  * 
 Tuesday\, March 10\, 6-7:30 pm – (caregivers of) preK-4th grade\n  * Tues
 day\, March 24\, 6-7:30 pm – (caregivers of) 5th-8th grade https://www.ev
 entbrite.com/e/5th-8th-grade-caregiver-sex-education-workshop-its-that-ea
 sy-tickets-1527604459059?utm-campaign=social&utm-content=attendeeshare&ut
 m-medium=discovery&utm-term=listing&utm-source=cp&aff=ebdsshcopyurl\n\nPl
 ease direct any additional questions to Hallie Cohen - hcohen@ywca-ens.or
 g mailto:hcohen@ywca-ens.org\n\nYou do not need to be a D65 family to att
 end\, this event is open to all!
CATEGORIES:Church-&-Dodge,Community-Event,Family-Friendly
