SUMMARY: Reading the Cards: A Tarot Study Group
DESCRIPTION:Picking up a tarot deck for the first time can feel overwhelm
 ing. Seventy-eight cards\, all that symbolism\, and no idea where to begi
 n. The good news? You don't need to memorize anything to start reading. Y
 ou just need a little guidance and a willingness to look closely at what'
 s in front of you.\n\nIn this hands-on workshop\, participants will use S
 tefanie Caponi's Guided Taro https://bookendsandbeginnings.com/book/97805
 93435649 t as a roadmap to start reading cards with confidence. Rather th
 an memorizing textbook definitions\, we'll explore exercises from the boo
 k that help you develop your own relationship with the cards using intuit
 ion\, observation\, and storytelling.\n\nThe box set includes a Rider Wai
 te Smith deck\, which is the foundation most modern tarot decks are built
  on. Learning with this deck gives you a visual language that transfers t
 o nearly any other deck you pick up down the road\, making it an especial
 ly smart starting point for anyone planning to continue learning or take 
 future workshops.\n\nYou'll leave with practical skills you can use immed
 iately: how to do a simple reading for yourself\, how to interpret what y
 ou see (not just what you've been told a card means)\, and a framework fo
 r continued practice at home.\n\nNo experience necessary. You don't need 
 to "believe" in anything\, just bring your curiosity.
