SUMMARY: 5th-8th Grade Caregiver Sex Education Workshop: It's That Easy
DESCRIPTION:This workshop is for parents\, caregivers\, and family member
 s who want to deepen their knowledge about healthy sexual development\, s
 exual identity\, and relationships and how to discuss these topics with t
 heir children and teens. Participate in a little bit of sex ed while your
  students receive it in school!\n\nLed by Hallie Cohen\, Training and Pre
 vention Coordinator for YWCA Evanston/North Shore and sex education consu
 ltant to D65\, this workshop will be an engaging\, interactive\, and disc
 ussion-based. During this workshop\, participants will:\n\n  * Explain ho
 w their own experience with sexuality education impacts how and what they
  share with their own children\;\n  * Identify the most important values 
 and messages they would like to pass on to their children about sexuality
 \;\n  * Gain an understanding of healthy sexual development for their chi
 ld’s age range\;\n  * Identify teachable moments during which they can sh
 are information and family values regarding sexuality.\n\nThis workshop w
 ill be held twice\, with the focus being on different age groups. If you 
 are unable to attend the date with the ideal focus for you\, feel free to
  register for the other date. You will surely get a lot out of it\, and s
 ome of the material will be the same.\n\n  * Tuesday\, March 10\, 6-7:30 
 pm – (caregivers of) preK-4th grade https://www.eventbrite.com/e/prek-4th
 -grade-caregiver-sex-education-workshop-its-that-easy-tickets-15276088822
 89?aff=oddtdtcreator\n  * Tuesday\, March 24\, 6-7:30 pm - (caregivers of
 ) 5th-8th grade\n\nPlease direct any additional questions to Hallie Cohen
  - hcohen@ywca-ens.org mailto:hcohen@ywca-ens.org\n\nYou do not need to b
 e a D65 family to attend\, this event is open to all!
CATEGORIES:Church-&-Dodge,Community-Event,Family-Friendly
