SUMMARY: Cooler by the Lake : True Tales from the Third Coast
DESCRIPTION:Experience Chicago’s most powerful stories\, told by the peop
 le who are shaping its future.\n\nCooler By the Lake brings together comm
 unity builders\, activists\, and creatives for an unforgettable night of 
 live storytelling. These aren’t just true tales\, they’re sparks of trans
 formation from the hearts of those making a difference. Authentic\, emoti
 onal\, sometimes hilarious\, and deeply human\, this show proves that sto
 rytelling is the heartbeat of our city.\n\nProduced in collaboration by\n
 \nJill Howe is the producer and founder of Story Sessions https://www.fac
 ebook.com/storysessionschicago \, a live storytelling series with real-ti
 me illustrations\, since 2013. She has performed widely across Chicagolan
 d\, served as a resident storyteller at the Field Museum\, led storytelli
 ng workshops for Newberry Library\, and presented a Naperville Tedx Talk 
 on vulnerability. Find more of her work at jillhowe.com https://jillhowe.
 com/\n\nSuzy Kahn Weinberg is the founder and executive producer of Big S
 houlders Stories http://www.bigshouldersstories.com/ \, a storytelling pr
 oduction company launched in 2019 to elevate and amplify the voices of th
 e people and organizations who work to change communities in Chicago. Suz
 y is also a co-producer of the long running monthly storytelling show\, I
 s this a thing? http://www.isthisathing.net/ now in its 12 year.
CATEGORIES:
